The paper discusses learning Bayesian networks, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of heuristic search-based algorithms also suggests a connection to optimization and combinatorial algorithms (cs.DM). The focus on finding high-quality solutions quickly and improving incumbent solutions aligns with the subfield of anytime algorithms (cs.SY). Finally, the use of Bayesian networks involves information theory (cs.IT).
